FBIS4-55599 "dreeu096_c_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-096 Daily Report 13 May 1994 CZECH REPUBLIC Former HSDMS Deputy Vlcek Joins Left Bloc Former HSDMS Deputy Vlcek Joins Left Bloc AU1705152194 Prague RUDE PRAVO in Czech 13 May 94 p 2 AU1705152194 Prague RUDE PRAVO Czech BFN [Unattributed report in the "By Telex" column] [Text] Deputy Z. Vlcek has become a new member of the Left Bloc deputies' club and the Left Bloc Party [LBS]. LBS Deputy Chairman J. Ortman announced this at a news conference on Thursday [12 May]. Vlcek stood for election for the Association for the Republic-Republican Party of Czechoslovakia and transferred to the Movement for Self-Governing Democracy-Society of Moravia and Silesia [HSDMS] but, since the HSDMS was established, had never joined the club.
